Incident.Summary: On 1/19/2023 I was dispatched to 1401 Pulaski Highway, Edgewood MD for a report of a robbery.

IncidentSuppNarrative.NarrativeText: ATTACHMENTS: Witness Statements Chain of Custody for Knife SUSPECTS Khalel Washington (B/M, DOB: 3/8/2004) VICTIM Charles Little Jr. (B/M, DOB: 9/18/1996) Scene Processing: Photos were taken of exterior Chinese Food store Photos taken of blood Splatter in Store Photos taken of interior of Liquor store where crime occurred NARRATIVE On 1/19/2023 at approximately 1954 hours, I was dispatched to 1401 Pulaski Highway, Edgewood MD 21040 for a possible attempted robbery. Upon my arrival, at 1401 Pulaski Highway Unit D, I made contact with Harford County Deputies who advised there was a victim in the restaurant with a laceration to the face. EMS was contacted, and I asked the subject for his name. He identified himself a Khalel Washington, Black/Male. I asked Washington what happened, and he stated that he was just walking through the woods when some guys jumped him and cut his face. I attempted to ask Washington for a description or direction of travel for the suspects, and he began to get irate and yelling for EMS to expedite. Washington was stating he was feeling woozy and was starting to lose memory of the events. I stopped questioning and walked outside to obtain photos of the scene. While walking outside I was advised by a Harford County Deputy that the original victim Washington was actually the suspect who attempted to rob another person around the corner. I walked to the Woodbridge Liquors located at the same address and made contact with Deputy First Class Burgess who handed me the knife which caused the laceration on Washingtons face. The owner of the knife was Charles Little Jr. Little stated he was speaking with Washington and another party through the selling app Offer up. They had coordinated to meet at 1706 Crimson Tree Way, Edgewood Md for the selling of a PS5. Little advised when he got on scene he was met by Washington and another unknown individual. Both parties advised Little that this was a robbery and to give up his money. Little advised he did not have any cash on his person. Washington and the other unknown party threatened to kill Little while reaching in their waistband. Washington then asked Little if he had a bank card to withdraw cash, Little replied yes and Washington got into the car and told Little to drive to a bank. Little drove to the MT Bank located in the Woodbridge Shopping Center. While en route Little advised he texted his mother robbery. After typing in the wrong pin at the bank Little suggested they go into the Liquor store to withdraw money. Both parties entered the Liquor storeand Little attempted to withdraw money. While stalling at the ATM, Littles wife Amber Eaton and sister-in-law Alicia Eaton ran into the store swinging a bat at Washington. An altercation ensued in the Liquor store and Washington ended up taking the bat. Washington ran out the store and attempted to come back into the store. Little, his wife, and sister-in-law were attempting to hold the door close to keep Washington out the store. Washington grabbed the door and Little stated he saw Washington reach in his waistband and say Im about to flip it out on you, you dont want to die over $20, give me that money. At that point Little reached for his pocket knife and cut Washington across the face. Washington then ran around the corner to the China Haste store and asked for EMS. I request this case remain open pending investigation and charging from CID. All events occurred in Harford County Maryland.

IncidentSuppNarrative.NarrativeText: On January 19, 2023, I was requested to assist the Maryland State Police Bel Air Barrack and TFC Arment with an assault and possible robbery investigation. Upon being contacted, I was requested to respond to Johns Hopkins Bayview Medical Center in Baltimore City to interview Khalel Washington who had been transported to that location after being cut or stabbed. At that time, no additional details were provided and I was unaware of what exactly Washingtons involvement was in the incident. Upon my arrival at Bayview, I made contact with Trooper Montgomery who followed the ambulance from the scene to the hospital. Tpr. Montgomery did not have all of the details, but informed me that it was believed Washington was involved in some sort of attempted robbery and that he had been cut in the process. After speaking to Tpr. Montgomery, I interviewed Washington. Interview with Kalel Washington Washington, Khalel Juwan African American, Male, DOB: 03/08/2004 1709 Crimson Tree Apt. B, Edgewood, MD 21040 Upon entering Washingtons room, I immediately observed that he had a large laceration above his right eye that extended below his left eye. I then began speaking with Washington and identified myself as an investigator with the Maryland State Police and Washington immediately stated he wanted to tell me what happened. I stopped him from proceeding and advised him that I would like to record the interview and he agreed. As soon as the recording started, I reintroduced myself and asked Washington to identify himself. He proceeded by telling me his first and last name immediately followed by Am I getting locked up? I informed Washington that I still was not sure exactly what occurred and that I was there to get his account of what happened. I also informed him that I had no reason to place him under arrest at that time. According to Washington, he was walking through the woods near Woodbridge Way when he bumped into a fiend or drug addict who then sliced him then ran away. Washington stated nothing else had occurred prior to this that would have caused the subject to cut him, just that he was upset that Washington physically bumped into him. Washington stated it was a very brief encounter and he was unable to see the subject that cut him. He stated he just knew it was a junky because he had drugs on him and he could tell he had recently lost weight and had open sores. Otherwise, Washington was unable to recollect any details about the subject or exactly what occurred. When asked why he was at the location, Washington stated he was heading to the store to get liquor, but then said Im lying. I was trying to get some leafs from any store in the area that sold it. He could not recall if he had ever made it to the store. He would then advise that he was headed home. Washington had nothing additional to add at the time and the recorded interview was concluded. Prior to leaving, I obtained photographs of Washingtons injury. I also positively identified Washington through a photograph obtained from the Maryland Motor Vehicle Administration. Additional Actions After interviewing Washington, I made contact with TFC Arment who was at the scene of the incident. We discussed the facts of the case and determined that no arrests would be made at that time. TFC Arment requested that I seize Washingtons cell phone as facts obtained at the scene indicated that the phone would more than likely contain evidence that would assist in the investigation. I had been told that Washingtons cell phone was located amongst his belongings on the floor. I informed Washington that we would be taking his phone and writing a search and seizure warrant for it and he had no objections. Washington provided the passcode to his phone as 537536. Washington was then left in the care of hospital staff. After leaving the hospital, I responded to the scene where the incident occurred and assisted TFC Arment. I then took Washingtons cell phone to the Bel Air Barrack where I completed the appropriate paperwork and submitted it as evidence. This concludes my involvement in the case at this time.

SCENE PROCESSING: Maryland State Police Crime Scene Technician J. Myer responded to the scene and conducted scene processing. NEIGHBORHOOD CHECKS: Due to the nature of this incident no checks were conducted. NARRATIVE: On January 19, 2023, Tfc. Arment #6828 of the Maryland State Police Criminal Enforcement Division - North Central Region Investigators was requested to respond to 1401 Pulaski Highway, Edgewood, Maryland to assist Troopers on scene with an attempted robbery. Tfc. Arment arrived at scene and was debriefed by Troopers of case details. Tfc. Arment completed numerous investigative tasks while on scene. While on scene Tfc. Arment learned additional pertinent details in reference this case. Tfc. Arment learned the following: - Interview was conducted with Kevin Docasbury Terrell Jr. (B/M DOB: 10/24/1991) -Terrell Jr. informed Tfc. Arment that he had arranged for the purchase of Playstation video game console via OfferUp (a mobile marketplace application) prior to this incident - Terrell Jr. willingly provided Tfc. Arment with his cellular device to show the details of the transaction. Tfc. Arment observed Terrell Jr. communicating via text with a subject identified as Tae - Tfc. Arment observed Terrell Jr. arrange for the purchase to take place electronically - Tfc. Arment observed Terrell Jr. arrange for a friend, whom he identified as his brother to retrieve the Playstation - Tfc. Arment observed the Tae subject direct Terrell Jr. to the address 1706 Crimson Tree and ask Terrell Jr. what type of vehicle he would be in - Tfc. Arment observed Terrell Jr. respond with Ok white suv - Tfc. Arment observed the Tae subject provide the phone number 443-756-8153 to make contact with Tfc. Arment conducted further investigation into the phone number 443-756-8153 in attempt to identify possible individuals associated with that phone number. At the time of this report, no further leads were developed. It should be noted, Terrell Jr. was cooperative with Troopers on scene and readily provided his cellular device to confirm the details of his recollection of events. Tfc. Arment then made contact with the subject identified by Terrell Jr. as his brother. That subject was identified as the victim in this incident, Charles Little Jr. (B/M DOB: 09/18/1996). While speaking with Little Jr., Tfc. Arment learned the following: - Little Jr. was asked by a friend, identified as Terrell Jr. to help him pick up a Playstation video game console - Terrell Jr. and Little Jr. are not relatives - Terrell Jr. does not reside in Harford County - Little Jr. lives in the area and was asked to help because he lives closer - Little Jr. drives a white Kia SUV bearing Maryland registration 4ED4777 - Little Jr. drove to the area of 1706 Crimson Tree Way, Edgewood, Maryland to pick up the Playstation for Terrell Jr. at around 1900 hours Little Jr., hereinafter referred to as VICTIM, arrived at the predetermined location and was approached by two male subjects. The events that transpired afterwards are detailed in the initial report authored by Trooper First Class Henry #6366. Additional details learned by Tfc. Arment are as follows: - The VICTIMs family members were able to determine his location via location sharing services on the VICTIMs cellular device - The VICTIM reiterated numerous times that he was in fear for his life and the lives of his family members who responded to the scene - Tfc. Arment observed surveillance video footage depicting the VICTIM standing at an ATM and a subject identified as Khalel Washington (B/M DOB: 03/08/2004) standing behind the VICTIM - Washington, hereinafter referred to as SUSPECT, was wearing a black ski mask and black jacket While conducting scene processing, Maryland State Police Crime Scene Technician Myer, recovered a black jacket from the scene. The SUSPECT was transported to Johns Hopkins Bayview Medical Center for his injuries. The details of the interaction with the SUSPECT at that facility are detailed in a supplemental report authored by Senior Trooper Orem #5656. Tfc. Arment completed numerous investigative tasks in the days following this incident. Tfc. Arment conducted the following: - Tfc. Arment authored a search and seizure warrant on the cellular device recovered by Senior Trooper Orem #5656. The search and seizure warrant was signed by the Honorable Judge Clara Campbell of the Cecil County District Court - Tfc. Arment coordinated with the Harford County Sheriffs Office Crime Suppression Unit/Intel Group and learned that the suspect in this case was the subject of an ongoing investigation involving the distribution of controlled dangerous substances in Harford County - Harford County Sheriffs Office Crime Suppression Unit/Intel Group notified Tfc. Arment that surveillance was being conducted at Washingtons residence located at 1709 Crimson Tree Way, Edgewood, Maryland - Tfc. Arment consulted with the Harford County States Attorney Office, resulting in Tfc. Arment completing an application for statement of charges An arrest warrant for the suspect in this case was obtained, charging Khalel Washington with numerous felonies including armed robbery and armed carjacking. Investigators coordinated with MSAT for service of the arrest warrant. Further coordination with allied agencies was conducted, and on January 25, 2023, North Central Region Investigators and members of the U.S. Marshals, MSAT, Harford County Sheriffs Office, and MSP Bel Air Barrack took custody of Washington at his residence without incident. Washington was transported to the Harford County Detention Center, where an initial appearance was conducted. Washington was subsequently held without bond. Case closed by arrest. Events occurred in Harford County, Maryland.

ATTACHMENTS: PlayStation Advertisement, OfferUp Profile, OfferUp Advertisements NARRATIVE: Tfc. Arment #6828 of the Maryland State Police Criminal Enforcement Division - North Central Region Investigators has completed additional investigative tasks in reference to this investigation. These tasks and results are outlined below: Tfc. Arment conducted additional investigation into OfferUp and the posted advertisement for the PlayStation video game console. Tfc. Arment utilized a confidential law enforcement database and located the advertisement (See Attachments - PlayStation Advertisement) Tfc. Arment observed the advertisement to be posted by a profile with the username Tae Tfc. Arment observed additional information regarding the profile Tae: Tae OfferUp seller ID #: 143378175 / Email: montae002@icloud.com / Location: Parkville, Maryland (See Attachments - OfferUp Profile) Tfc. Arment observed numerous advertisements posted by the Tae profile. Tfc. Arment observed a date when the PlayStation was advertised as 01/17/2023 (See Attachments - OfferUp Advertisements) Tfc. Arment learned of an interaction between Harford County Sheriffs Office (HCSO) deputies and a subject identified as Damontae Ferguson (B/M DOB: 07/10/2001). Damontae Ferguson provided HCSO with the phone number: 443-756-8153. This was the same number Tfc. Arment #6828 identified as belonging to Tae during the initial investigation, on the cellular device belonging to Kevin Docasbury Terrell Jr. (B/M DOB: 10/24/1991). On April 19, 2023, Tfc. Arment received a forensic download of the cellular device seized by investigators. Tfc. Arment reviewed the forensic download and outlined pertinent information regarding this investigation below: Phone number 443-756-8153 identified with contact name Tay Instant Messages between 443-756-8153 and Khalel Washington on date of the incident (01/19/2023) Sent from Washington to Ferguson: No da 1709 crimson tree Sent from Ferguson to Washington: Open the door Sent from Ferguson to Washington: Going to the hospital Instant Messages between 667-757-0073 (Sarah)and Washington on 01/06/2023: From 667-757-0073 (Sarah) to Washington: Just to hold my shit for pretection cool but to hold it to rob a nigga not at all this shit is registered not like its a fucking toy Khalil! You need a gun to rob niggas get one of them from ur homeboys! Tfc. Arment conducted further investigation into Damontae Ferguson and observed a last known address at 1603 Wentworth Avenue, Parkville, Maryland. This location corresponds with the location of the registration for the OfferUp profile. All events occurred in Harford County, Maryland Case reopened.

NARRATIVE: On May 23, 2023, a Harford County Grand Jury indicted Damontae Ferguson on numerous charges related to conspiracy to commit armed robbery, kidnapping, and carjacking. An arrest warrant was issued for Ferguson. All events occurred in Harford County, Maryland.
